{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0652c20a6b1e30b238608701299fccb6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"From `src/db.ts:86-92` and the trust state assignment logic:\n\n```ts\nexport type ClusterTrustState =\n  | \"static_verified\"   // all facts statically verified\n  | \"llm_verified\"      // all facts LLM-verified\n  | \"partial_static\"    // some facts rejected in static verification\n  | \"partial_llm\"       // some facts rejected in LLM verification\n  | \"untrusted\";\n```\n\n**`static_verified`** — set when a factsheet passes static-only verification with zero rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:133`, `src/clusterRefresh.ts:176-181`):\n```ts\nconst trustState = verification.rejectedFacts.length === 0 ? \"static_verified\" : \"partial_static\";\n```\n\n**`partial_llm`** — set when LLM verification runs but some facts were rejected or not promoted (`src/cluster.ts:221-222`):\n```ts\nconst rejectedFacts = [...verification.rejectedFacts, ...llmVerification.rejectedFacts];\nllmVerification.factsheet.omitted_facts = rejectedFacts.length;\nconst trustState = rejectedFacts.length === 0 ? \"llm_verified\" : \"partial_llm\";\n```\n\n**`llm_verified`** — set when LLM verification runs and zero facts were rejected (`src/cluster.ts:222`).\n\n**When each occurs:**\n\n| Trust State | When |\n|---|---|\n| `static_verified` | `cluster_prepare` with `verification_mode: \"static\"` (the default) — static verifier accepts all facts, no LLM step |\n| `llm_verified` | `cluster_prepare` with `verification_mode: \"llm\"` — LLM verifier promoted every fact to `VERIFIED` |\n| `partial_llm` | `cluster_prepare` with `verification_mode: \"llm\"` — LLM verifier rejected at least one fact; some omitted |\n\n`partial_static` follows the same pattern for the static-only path."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":187,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3879,"cache_read_input_tokens":91923},"s